Q.22 Create a form.jsp which accepts two numbers from user and sends numbers to other jsp page in which compare two numbers using JSTL tag and display the largest number.
 Ans:
 Form.jsp:
 <%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1"
    pageEncoding="ISO-8859-1"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>Insert title here</title>
</head>
<body>
<form action="Display_Ass_22.jsp">
Enter Number : <input type="number" name="num1"><br>
Enter Number : <input type="number" name="num2"><br>
<input type="submit" value="Check">
</form>
</body>
</html>
Display.jsp:
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1"
    pageEncoding="ISO-8859-1"%>
    <%@ taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core" prefix="c" %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>Insert title here</title>
</head>
<body>
<c:choose>
  <c:when test="${param.num1>param.num2}">
    <h3>${param.num1} is bigger than ${param.num2}</h3>
  </c:when>
  <c:when test="${param.num2>param.num1}">
    <h3>${param.num2} is bigger than ${param.num1}</h3>
  </c:when>
  <c:otherwise>
   <h3>${param.num1} and ${param.num2} are equal </h3>
  </c:otherwise>
</c:choose>
</body>
</html>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q.23 Create a form.jsp which accepts username & password and submits the data to other jsp page which checks if the password is valid then sends the response to 
     success.jsp page which displays a message as "Valid Login" otherwise sends the response to failure.jsp which displays message "Invalid login" .Use JSTL tag 
     to compare.
 Ans:
Form.jsp:
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1"
    pageEncoding="ISO-8859-1"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>Insert title here</title>
</head>
<body>
<form action="check_Ass_23.jsp">
Username <input type="text" name="UN"><br>
Password <input type="password" name="PASS"><br>
<input type="submit" value="Logn in">
 </form>
</body>
</html>
Check.jsp:
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1"
    pageEncoding="ISO-8859-1"%>
     <%@ taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core" prefix="c" %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>Insert title here</title>
</head>
<body>
<c:choose>
      <c:when test="${param.PASS=='1234'}">
       <c:redirect url="/success_Ass_23.jsp"></c:redirect>
      </c:when>
      <c:otherwise>
       <c:redirect url="/failure_Ass_23.jsp"></c:redirect>
       </c:otherwise>
    </c:choose>
</body>
</html>
Success.jsp:
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1"
    pageEncoding="ISO-8859-1"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>Insert title here</title>
</head>
<body>
<h4>"Valid Login"</h4>
</body>
</html>
Failure.jsp:
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1"
    pageEncoding="ISO-8859-1"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>Insert title here</title>
</head>
<body>
<h4>"Invalid login" </h4>
</body>
</html>
